{
  "nbformat": 4,
  "nbformat_minor": 5,
  "metadata": {
    "kernelspec": {
      "name": "maxima",
      "display_name": "Maxima",
      "language": "maxima"
    },
    "aximar": {}
  },
  "cells": [
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "# Monte Carlo Methods\n\nMonte Carlo methods use **random simulation** to estimate quantities that\nmay be difficult or impossible to compute analytically. This notebook\ndemonstrates several classic applications: estimating $\\pi$, studying\nconvergence rates, verifying the Central Limit Theorem, computing\nintegrals, and constructing bootstrap confidence intervals.\n\nWe use the `numerics` package for vectorized random number generation\nand array operations, and `ax-plots` for visualization.",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "load(\"numerics\")$\nload(\"ax-plots\")$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 89,
      "outputs": []
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "## Estimating Pi\n\nThe classic Monte Carlo estimate of $\\pi$: scatter $N$ random points\nuniformly in the unit square $[0,1]^2$ and count how many fall inside\nthe quarter unit circle ($x^2 + y^2 \\le 1$). The ratio of inside\npoints to total points approximates $\\pi/4$, so\n\n$$\\hat{\\pi} = 4 \\cdot \\frac{\\text{count inside}}{N}$$",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Generate N random points in [0,1)^2 */\nN : 10000$\npts : np_rand([N, 2])$\nx : np_col(pts, 0)$\ny : np_col(pts, 1)$\n\n/* Distance from origin for each point */\nd : np_sqrt(np_add(np_pow(x, 2), np_pow(y, 2)))$\n\n/* Count points inside the quarter unit circle */\ninside_mask : np_less_equal(d, 1.0)$\ncount_inside : np_sum(inside_mask)$\n\npi_estimate : 4.0 * count_inside / N$\nprint(\"Monte Carlo pi estimate:\", pi_estimate)$\nprint(\"True pi:\", float(%pi))$\nprint(\"Error:\", abs(pi_estimate - float(%pi)))$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 90,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Monte Carlo pi estimate: 3.1704\nTrue pi: 3.141592653589793\nError: 0.02880734641020677"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "/* Scatter plot: blue = inside circle, red = outside */\nx_in  : np_to_list(np_extract(inside_mask, x))$\ny_in  : np_to_list(np_extract(inside_mask, y))$\noutside_mask : np_logical_not(inside_mask)$\nx_out : np_to_list(np_extract(outside_mask, x))$\ny_out : np_to_list(np_extract(outside_mask, y))$\n\nax_draw2d(\n  color=blue, name=\"Inside\", marker_size=2,\n  points(x_in, y_in),\n  color=red, name=\"Outside\", marker_size=2,\n  points(x_out, y_out),\n  title=sconcat(\"Pi Estimate: \", string(pi_estimate), \" (N=\", string(N), \")\"),\n  xlabel=\"x\", ylabel=\"y\",\n  aspect_ratio=true,\n  grid=true\n)$",
      "metadata": {},
      "execution_count": 91,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "data": {
